result.execSummary:
On one or more charges, the deferred prosecution or sentencing agreement(s) on this case were fulfilled, and the charge(s) were dismissed.

The defendant Joseph M Graf was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Narcotic Drugs, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(am).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.
Defendant is to comply with any rules/recommendations as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.   DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.

1:10 pm case called. Defendant Joseph M Graf in court with attorney Kristina M. Sanders-Brown.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Agreement stated on the record by Attorney Blader. State moves to amend count 1 to Possession of Schedule I or II Narcotics in violation of 961.341(3g)(am).   Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: No Contest to Count 1 & No Contest to Count 2.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Statement by defendant. Court makes statement prior to sentencing.  COUNT 1-Court sentences the defendant to: SWD and places on probation for a period of 30 months. CONDITIONS: 100 days WCJ, with Huber, No Good Time Credit. No Credit for time served to begin no later than February 26, 2016. AODA and follow through,    The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. $200 Drug Buy Money, Costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. Terms of Agent. DNA sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice. COUNT 2-  Court accepts plea stays JOC and accepts terms and conditions of PPDA.  Matter stayed for 30 months. Court admonishes the defendant regarding bond. Appeal Rights Given.
